{
  "schema_version": "parallax-signature-pack/v1",
  "id": "lucent.python-idioms",
  "name": "lucent Python stdlib idioms",
  "version": "0.1.0",
  "status": "experimental",
  "description": "A lucent supplement to the parallax callee pack: common Python-standard-library call idioms the reference pack does not cover (pathlib file I/O, os.environ, hashlib, threading, time.sleep, socketserver, keyring). Python-only, high precision — every rule keys on a module-qualified name or a distinctive pathlib method name, both safe against the local-variable false positives a bare-name match would cause.",
